🏛️ The "Campus Echoes" Generation Prompt
System Role: You are an expert Front-end Developer specializing in immersive, minimalist storytelling interfaces.

Task: Create a single-file "Campus Memories Map" interactive webpage for Bansal Institute of Science & Technology (BIST), Bhopal.

Design Requirements:

Aesthetic: Dark-themed "Midnight" UI with a Glassmorphism finish. Use a background noise/grain texture, deep blacks (#020202), and subtle radial glows behind the main map.

Hero Section:

A minimalist header with a pulsing status dot (red/green).

Large, elegant typography using "Inter" or "Outfit" with italicized emphasis for the word "Memories."

A "Scroll to Explore" indicator with a vertical animated line.

The Interactive Map:

Display a provided aerial image of the campus in a card with a subtle border-glow.

Place 4 interactive "Pins" using absolute positioning.

Pin Mechanics: The pins should pulse (CSS scale animation) and include a teardrop shape or a location icon. On hover, show a tooltip label (e.g., "Central Library").

The Memory Interaction:

When a pin is clicked, trigger a Modal Overlay with a backdrop blur (backdrop-filter: blur(12px)).

The modal must contain: A location-specific photo (top), a Title, a Subtitle, a short nostalgic description, and a "Mood Badge" (e.g., "Mood: Emotional" with color coding).

Gamification & UX:

Add a "Discovery Counter" (e.g., "0/4 Memories Found").

Include a Toast Notification system that pops up when a user finds a new location or completes the map.

Smooth entry animations (Reveal on scroll) for the sections.

Technical Requirements:

Use only a single HTML file (CSS in <style>, JS in <script>).

Focus on accessibility (Keyboard navigation for pins, ARIA labels).

Ensure mobile responsiveness (stack stats, scale map pins for touch).

Use CSS variables for colors (Red for ground, Blue for Library, Orange for Canteen).